observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the management agreed to:
Properly plan programs, projects, activities implemented to refrain from reprogramming of funds to other purposes and utilize  the planned programs and projects that are related to the current year’s  20% Development Fund programs and projects pursuant to Sections 3.2.2 and 3.2.3 of JMC of the Department of DBM/DOF and DILG No. 1 dated November 4, 2020 in order to achieve the intended purposes for which the fund was appropriated;
Ensure prompt and full implementation of the 20% development projects and programs during the current year;
Stop using funds appropriated/intended for the planned programs and projects in the  20% DF to other expenses  pursuant to Section 4(1) of  P.D. No. 1445  otherwise  they  will  be disallowed in audit;
Direct the Local Development Council to prepare Supplemental Investment Program to be approved by the Local Sanggunian every time there is a reprogramming of  the PPAs already approved in the Annual Investment Plan of the municipality and furnish the Audit Team of the copy thereof.
Strict compliance of  Section 287 of R.A. No. 7160 and   Sections  3.0 – 5.0 of  the  DILG/ DBM  Joint   Memorandum   Circular No. 2017-1  dated February 22, 2017.

We recommended and the management agreed to:
Direct the Municipal Health Officer and/or concerned RHU personnel to furnished the Municpal OIC-Accountant, the documents necessary to record the receipt and distribution of vaccines, ancillaries and supplies Inventory Report  or its equivalent in relation to the vaccination program;
Direct the Municipal OIC-Accountant to record using the perpetual inventory system, the vaccines received and its distribution as reported by the LGU to DOH-CHD; and draw journal entry voucher for the applicable inventory accounts to record the remaining supplies of vaccines in stock at December 31,2021.

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to immediately submit the aforementioned supporting documents to enable the Audit Team to evaluate the BGCM, Trust Fund and LDRRMF transactions amounting to ₱14.791 million;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to throughly verify each disbursement as to the completeness and propriety of the supporting documents to strengthen internal control in the disbursement process; and

Adhere to the procedures and requirements provided in Section 4 (6) of P.D. 1445, Items 9.2 and 9.2.5 of COA  Circular No. 2012-001  dated  June 14, 2012  and  GPPB  Circular  No. 01-2020 dated April 6, 2020 particularly in the conduct of emergency procurement under the Bayanihan Act.

We recommended and the Management agreed to the following:
Maximize utilization of the GAD funds through the implementation and regular monitoring of GAD related programs, and that projects and activities that addressed gender issues and women empowerment and gender equality should be prioritized  in order to attain the objective for which the funds are provided in conformity with Section1.2 of Joint Circular No. 2004-1 of DBM, NEDA and NCRFW and Section 4.1 (c.1.4) of Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2013-01 of PCW, DILG, DBM and NEDA;
Refrain from realignment of funds to other purposes and utilize  only the planned programs and projects that are related to the appropriated fund  pursuant  Section 4(1) of P.D. No. 1445 ;

Demand the Municipal Officials concerned to submit the Deed of Absolute Sale from the Landowners; 

Prioritize the titling of the subject  lots in the name of the Municipality to establish ownership and full control thereof;

After completion of the TCT, submit copy of TCT and other documentary requirement/s to the Audit Team to avoid audit suspension or disallowance of the said transactions; and

Henceforth,  comply  strictly  with  the   Sections  4(6)   and   39(2)    of   P.D.  No. 1445 and  Section  449  of  GAAM, Volume I  and  Section 13.1 of COA  Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012.

Ensure prompt and full implementation of the 20% development projects and programs during the current year;  

Proper planning of programs and projects should be made to refrain from reprogramming of funds to other purposes and utilize only the planned programs and projects that are related to the current year’s  20% Development Fund programs and projects in order to achieve the intended purposes for which the fund was appropriated;

Stop using funds appropriated/intended for the planned programs and projects in the  20% DF  pursuant to  Section 4(1) of  P.D. No. 1445  otherwise  they  will  be disallowed in audit; and

Strict compliance of  Section 287 of R.A. No. 7160 and Section 5 of DILG/DBM and JMC No. 2011-1  dated April 13, 2011 and Sections  3.0 – 4.0 of  the  DILG/ DBM  Joint   Memorandum   Circular No. 2017-1  dated February 22, 2017.

