We recommended to Management the following:
Return the unexpended/unutilized amount of the fund transferred by the barangays to the respective barangays in order for them to implement their own developmental programs and projects, if any;
Strictly comply with Section 5 of the DILG/DBM Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2011-1 dated April 13, 2011 and Section 2(a) of RA 7160 in granting local autonomy to local government units specifically the barangay government.

We recommended to Management the following:
Replenish  the amount of the fund to the 30% QRF and require the Municipal Accountant and  the OIC, MDRRMO to reclassify programs, projects and activities of LDRRMF properly;
Strictly comply with Sections 5.3 and 6.3 of the NDRRMC, DBM and DILG Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2013-1 dated March 25, 2013 and Section 5.1.2 of COA Circular No. 2012-002 dated September 12, 2012.

Require  immediate   liquidation of cash advances  totalling   ₱730,079.80     as of December 31, 2016;

Refrain from granting additional cash advances unless the previous cash advance has been settled/liquidated;

Strengthen monitoring controls to ensure prompt and adequate documentation on the liquidation of cash advances; 

Require an official/employee who intends to be separated from the service due to reassignment/transfer/retirement to secure the necessary clearances from accountabilities;

Withhold the salary of concerned officials and employees and institute other sanctions to those who failed to liquidate their cash advances within the prescribed period; and
Henceforth, comply strictly with provisions of Section 89 of PD 1445 and COA Circular No. 97-002 dated February 10, 1997.

Prioritize the titling of the subject  lots in the name of the Municipality to establish ownership and full control thereof;

After completion of the TCT,  submit copy of TCT and other documentary requirement/s to the Audit Team to avoid audit suspension or disallowance of the said transactions; and

Henceforth, comply strictly with the Sections 4(6) and 58 of  P.D. No. 1445 and Section 449 of GAAM, Volume I.

Submit legal basis for granting of gasoline allowance to SB Members as well as the giving of gasoline to various barangays out of the SB appropriation, otherwise, require the concerned municipal officials to refund the amount pertaining thereto;

Stop the practice of granting gasoline allowance to any municipal official receiving Monthly RATA and has no government vehicle being assigned to them as well as  in giving gasoline to various barangays without appropriation;

Charge gasoline expenses directly to fuel, oil and lubricants inventory and expense account and not from Other MOOE to observe proper principles of accounting and auditing;

Require the driver to submit  properly accomplished Driver’s Trip Ticket  before approving it and see to it that  this will be supported to government motor vehicle only;

Designate personnel to monitor fuel consumption and submit regularly the Monthly Report of Fuel Consumption and Monthly Report of Official Travel; and

Henceforth, strictly comply with the provisions of Sections 340(e) and 361(f-g) of GAAM, Vol. I.

Immediately form the members of the Municipality’s SWMB;

Direct the Municipal SWMB to convene regularly to enable efficient and effective performance of its functions; and

Henceforth, strictly comply with Section 12 of R.A. No. 9003.

